Daily menu of an obese child: no breakfast and dinner sausages
More than one-third of children between the ages of 9 and 13 have problems with overweight, where overweight affects 9% of the school population and obesity 5%.
Obese children mostly come from families with an unhealthy lifestyle, according to current research.
It is again demonstrated the importance of the environment where it is grown for a healthy development of the person, as well as the models that serve as reference.
At the table, obsessed children feed, for example, on sausages at least twice as often as children from normal-weight families.
For dinner, more than 19% of obese people had chips the day before the analysis, which is linked to the “Obesity is not a coincidence” prevention program.
In families of overweight children there is no habit of playing sports, which is applicable to most current families, where only 15% of children responded that their parents, at least once a week, find time for physical exercise.
Survey of 900 children
The survey was conducted at the end of last school year and involved nearly 900 basic education children from all over the Czech Republic.
It was already the second edition of the program of "Obesity is not a coincidence", which supports the General Health Insurance Company and Unilever company.
So far, more than 12,000 children have participated in the project from the 4th to the 8th grade.
A proper diet and enough exercise in the family are determining factors, which significantly decrease the number of overweight and even obese children.
“Only half of the children surveyed have answered that they have five meals a day according to the regimen: breakfast, lunch, lunch, snack and dinner, which is one of the basic conditions for a healthy diet,” one of the survey results said.
No breakfast but with sausage for dinner
Specialists warn that, in a healthy development, the details are also important, which also count, such as having a fixed time for breakfast with the family.
In the Czech Republic, however, only 23% of schoolchildren’s families have breakfast at the same time.
In most families, each eats breakfast alone.
But the worst thing was to find out that in 10% of households they don’t have breakfast.
Breakfast is, however, the basis of a correct daily diet.
The study shows that in families of obese children, insane chips are consumed much more often.
Almost everyone – regardless of weight – drinks sweet soft drinks on a daily basis (70%).
As a rule, more than 40% of the children surveyed do sport, however, among their parents this result is reduced to less than half, only 15%.
Make Your Diet
The next phase of the study allowed the chosen boys (204 boys and 172 girls from 13 schools) to create their own diets from all possible offers according to their tastes and opinions.
“The dietary preferences of Czech children between the ages of 12 and 15, from the point of view of healthy eating, are far from ideal.”
Among your favorite foods are pasta, meat and sweets
“It is above all alarming the popularity of sweet sodas,” the study’s final report warns.
As the main meal, take the palm pasta and follow closely the bird meat.
Practically, children always reject legumes and the taste for fish and vegetables is very low.
Changing to Healthy Habits
At the same time, the study shows that children are willing to change their eating habits if they receive the right information.
“In the control group of study participants, who completed the questionnaire after completing the prevention program ‘Obesity is not a coincidence’, there was in many cases a significant change in favor of the principles of healthy eating,” the study’s findings point out.
Attention is drawn, for example, to sweet sodas, where many children would begin to prefer normal running water.
Children would also more often choose poultry meat and fish for the main meal in the questionnaire and would restrict consumption of sweet food and flour derivatives.
