Need for Speed: The Run is an all-American game.
Reviewed
A trip, in principle carefree, is complicated by a series of inappropriate neglects of a routine trip during the morning shift.
To some extent it was possible to meet expectations, but this is of no use if, in reality, nothing extraordinary was intended to be done.
The new installment, to which The Run is added, aroused high expectations even before its release.
He promised that he would give new air to the old racing saga Need for Speed and, in the wake of what was shown, appears as a game that should not end up being an action genre once again.
We also felt curious to know how the scenes would look inserted, where the main character descends from the car and walks on his own foot.
As is often the case in the NFS series, the results do not vary much from what we expected.
There are races that can be considered acceptable, but in the total computation points are lost because of absurd failures, which have been appearing in the series for years.
In reality, they cannot even be called errors, but rather it is the incomprehensible misconception of programmers.
The adventure starts very well.
You are introduced to a story, whose protagonist, Jack, has certain personal problems; to solve them, he is offered to participate in an illegal race all over America.
You sit behind the wheel on the west coast, in San Francisco, and your mission is to get to New York first.
The idea is to offer something interesting.
The route is divided into ten stages and then more than fifty races.
It follows that each race takes place by a different route and the stages are located in different environments, which are quite diverse and interesting.
In this way, one does not even remotely feel that the game always offers the same.
Some of the environments are even pleasing to the eye, although the technical level of the graphic is equivalent to that of previous deliveries of the series.
Therefore, it is nothing from the other world.
But the walk through the desert, the autumn landscape or the high snow-covered mountains produce a very pleasant visual effect.
In addition, races are diversified from time to time by an atypical element.
So, for example, in the desert you find a sandstorm that diminishes visibility.
But in the mountains you must be careful not to bury an avalanche.
According to that, each of the races is very well developed.
There are only a couple of models, but that’s enough.
For a moment, you try to overtake a required number of rivals (normal in a classic race), then try to win time (timed classic duel) and then a duel against a single opponent awaits you.
In the middle of all this sometimes appears the police, which only makes things even more difficult.
The novelty is the landscapes outside the car.
Interactive animations are presented when Jack, in most cases, has to escape someone and you have to help him, always pressing the button right at the right time.
Nothing complicated.
It is surprising, however, that there are far fewer landscapes in the game than you would expect (in particular there are only three).
But the end result is positive, because this element does not become annoying and, in the context already mentioned, it is one of the elements that make the game more interesting.
The driving model follows in the footsteps of previous episodes.
That means that today it is no longer a big deal, but it cannot be said to be bad.
If you are looking for a realistic simulation, you can already search elsewhere.
But a race conceived with a lot of action suits quite this driving style, although we will be able to find something better among the games of the competition.
So far, all in order.
But the problems arise after a certain time.
Unlike the correct driving models, the same is no longer true for collisions.
From games of this type it is not expected to recreate complicated deformations and collisions, but in fact before a hit against any object, you can not predict how your car will react, with which everything is not in order.
It is typical that, when making a very tight overtaking or circulating the car with normal traffic, there are only slight rubbing, but in other almost identical situations, your car ends up doing uncontrolled pirouettes.
Or it even ends up totally destroyed.
Thanks to the reset system, there are no big problems, but it can get you in a bad mood.
Resets are programmed in such a way that when you crash or leave the track, the game returns you to the last rescue point on the track.
However, in each race only five resets are available.
If you consume all of them, you have to restart the race from the beginning.
So it's just a help in case something goes wrong, but it's not very reliable.
Sometimes, even reset does not help, it only helps to learn the given stage from memory.
A big disadvantage of the game is that the same facts are repeated in different places.
In some curves, for example, you have to enter in a specific way; otherwise, they are impossible to take.
Other times you will find somewhere "civil" vehicles always with the same configuration, even if you are the first, fifth or arrived five minutes before or after.
This makes you angry especially in situations, when you see that two cars that meet in opposite directions, your opponent advances without problems, but when you arrive, you must turn or brake.
It’s the same when you arrive, because it’s programmed because the “surprise” will always happen in front of your noses.
The opponents also have one more advantage.
Throughout the game you will reach places where, regardless of the moment, the same opponent will always be ahead of you in the same place.
This also happens at the end of the game, on a long bridge, which is even more shocking.
Your opponent must arrive before you, at any price.
When it goes in front of you, it makes it difficult for you to see the cars that come from the front, so at first you can rub the car.
You can understand the idea of creating a game with maximum doses of suspense and adrenaline, but the execution is so apparent that it will surely disappoint you right away.
And it’s a shame, because even if the travel model is simple, the game is fun and action-packed, so it’s often not possible to follow in detail what happens or where.
And it really doesn’t matter, whether the merit takes the idea with fifty exclusive tracks or qualifying in the race so that boredom doesn’t fit, or anything else.
An unusual idea is the change of cars during races.
You have to be aware of the gasoline supplies next to the road, because precisely there you have to change cars, although in the vast majority of cases you will have enough what you have.
The cars are divided into three categories.
Sports cars are suitable for urban areas, American strong cars for straight highways and exotic super sports cars for technical driving, for example on curved mountain roads.
In addition to the main narrative thread, there is also a parallel thread of challenges, that is, there are races in specific places that you will know through the stories.
Here you will get not only medals, but also experience points for your profile, which serves both challenges and stories.
Upon reaching the top level, the driver opens up several possibilities, starting with the car and finishing with funds for the profile.
At the same time, there is an online Autolog feature, which compares your results with those of other players and provides other community features.
One of the most difficult elements to understand is how the last race in history is made.
With the car you get to the tunnel of the metro (pass), where you run in the dark through the tracks (pass).
The speedometer marks you between 150 and 200 km / h (pass) and suddenly, from behind you the metro convoy arrives and takes you ahead without further ado.
In the editorial we will surely have a discussion about this for several days, about whether during the programming of the game none even thought a little or if the authors really take us for a bunch of fools.
The technical part of the game is nothing special, but at least the overall visual effects are in most cases pleasant, sometimes even superb.
What a pity that, in the most tense moments, the image quality is reduced and, sometimes, in a serious way.
This affects especially accidents where many participants are involved, when continuous image quality is no longer valid.
The audio is fine and the soundtrack is a matter of taste.
In order to please most of the youth group, the soundtrack belongs to the category "each of his father and mother", but it can be assumed that no one would buy the game just for their music.
The final feeling of Need for Speed: The Run is quite confusing.
If the game avoided absolutely silly mistakes, we would have trouble claiming that The Run is the best NFS game of recent years.
It feels like the game is not over.
The fun is assured, but be prepared because mistakes will hit you in the eyes with the force of airport reflectors.
