Modern post-gerra architecture is passionate, clear shapes, glass halls, brave curves and new building materials, typical of thinking about technical progress, for which the Austrian pavilion by architect Karl Schwanzer for the 1958 Brussels Universal Exhibition is a suitable and well-known example.
