The building was suitable but lacked the right spaces and technology for a museum; without any wall to hang art, nor a good atmosphere.
Nevertheless, it was used until contemporary art in Vienna had a new home.
The building has been empty since 2001 and is decaying more and more.
Currently, the architect Adolf Krischanitz reformed the pavilion, now calling it "House 21" and will be used in the future as a museum of contemporary art.
