He knew the project and the problem of the building, which disappeared with his transfer to Vienna in its change of use with generosity and ease.
In the current reforms there are big problems, the building was "an energy devourer," Krischanitz said.
The profile of the glass facade windows was changed, an insulating glass reinforced with fiberglass was installed and the glass ceiling was replaced by a special safety glass.
Thermal bridges and steel beams were reinforced or replaced and asbestos roofs were rehabilitated.
Two basements were used for the new use, a panel of light descending between the house and the street provides lighting, a bridge serves to enter the almost new building, but still the Schwanzer pavilion.
