"These changes would break the faith with those who maintain our army and would seriously damage the willingness."
The cuts would eventually reach combat troops, Panetta said.
"While funding for wartime in overseas contingency operations accounts is not directly affected by the abduction, war efforts would be negatively affected by severe disruptions in core budgets," Panetta said.
