The total vote count may also be made if at the end of the ordinary count it is established that the difference between the allegedly winning candidate and the second-placed candidate is equal to or less than a percentage point, provided that there is an express request from the representative of the political party whose candidate was second, in which case electoral packages that have been partially counted are excluded.
