Fujimori is admitted again for medical examinations
Former President Alberto Fujimori was admitted to a public hospital Tuesday to be evaluated for the loss of muscle strength in his legs, his GP said.
Fujimori, 72, who serves a sentence of 25 years in prison for human rights violations committed during his government (1990-2000), suffers from several ailments, including a cancer of the tongue for which he has been operated four times and which remains under control.
