Secretary Dionisio Pérez Jácome gives details of the plane crash in which the secretary of the governorate, Francisco Blake, and seven more people lost their lives
The Secretariat of Communications and Transport (SCT) reported that the results thrown over the accident where the secretary of state, Francisco Blake Mora, and seven other people lost their lives, indicate that the helicopter was directly impacted on the ground in complete structural integrity, without the pilot being able to attempt a forced landing.
