"Elements that appear to indicate that the unit had several contacts with the ground, the blades had contact with trees 25 meters away where the unit lost the fuselage."
He also reported that the unit was designed for 19 people, so it had the necessary requirements to transport the personnel.
In addition, he said that investigations in the impact area do not report the appearance of pieces on the ground.
"In a search they report that there are no parts or components of the ship elsewhere, the impact was presented in a structural way.
“The design of the helicopter was for 19 passengers, it had adequate requirements for transporting the passengers.
The terrain has a slope of seven degrees at 30 degrees of inclination.
