This was the work of the Cale<0xC3><0xB1>o who identified the corpse of Alfonso Cano
A lophoscopist from Cali went down in history as the man who confirmed the death of "Alfonso Cano".
The work of these officials is key.
On November 4, a lophoscopist from the CTI of Cali went on to history as the man who confirmed the identity of the highest head of the FARC: "Alfonso Cano", through the comparison of his fingerprints.
Of the seven lophoscopists who work in the section of the ITC, that week was the turn of "availability" to Eliazar González, a man from Puerto Tejada who has been working in the area of judicial investigation for 21 years.
At the beginning of his career, González worked in municipalities of Chocó, where he often had to spend more than five days in the jungle to reach the place where the corpses were to be identified.
In 2000 he moved to the capital of the Valley and, after completing the corresponding courses, specialized in lophoscopy, which is the study of friction skin, that is, of the palms of the hands and feet.
The week of the operation against alias Alfonso Cano Eliazar was warned to wear minimum clothes for three days.
Something big awaited him.
On Friday night he left for the Cauca in a helicopter from Palmyra.
He knew that he had to identify two corpses and that one of them was suspected to be from the man who was leading the world's oldest guerrilla, so he was asked to carry the decadactylar card of William Leon Sáenz (his real name).
However, when he arrived with the investigative team to the site where the corpse was, he did not recognize it because of its physical appearance, as it was very different from what he had seen in the media.
He was beardless, dressed like a local peasant, without glasses and much thinner.
But the fingerprints don't lie.
Accompanied by a Galtonian magnifying glass, ink, a transplanter and a flashlight, Eliazar compared the fingerprints of the corpse to those of the card.
His eye did not fail: it was "Alfonso Cano".
That same night, the man from Puerto Tejada was in charge of confirming to the Minister of Defense, Juan Carlos Pinzón, that he was indeed the chief of the FARC.
In Search of the Footprint
For a fingerprinter from Sijín de Cali, the recognition made by President Juan Manuel Santos to Eliazar González, at the press conference for the operation against "Cano", is very significant.
Many people do not know our work.
Fingerprinting is an exact science, with no margin for error, that can become key in the resolution of crimes.
In addition to identifying corpses, lophoscopists support investigations into crimes such as theft and murder and confirm the identity of the captured persons.
When captured, many criminals present false or undocumented ballots.
We take the fingerprint and search for them in the database.
The investigator said that in a case of theft, it was up to him to remove a piece of a wall from a house, because there the thief had supported his hand to pull out a safe full of jewelry and money.
“The walls are difficult because they are not suitable surfaces to make a fingerprint, but in that case we were able to get the fingerprint of the whole hand and identify the offender, who had participated in different thefts,” he recalled.
Fingerprints can also rule out or reaffirm suspects in homicide cases.
Recently they found a dead man, with bottles of liquor around him.
The investigation determined that a relative could be suspected of the crime and, indeed, a fingerprint on the bottle coincided.
Although this does not guarantee that it was the killer, it does place him at the scene of the crime.
A CTI fingerprinter explained that in the objects "the fingerprints are taken with chemical or physical reagents."
When they appear, a transplantator or ribbon is used to lift them.
After this, impressions are sent to the Asif, which is the criminal database, or to the Registry.
“The problem is that there are still many Colombians undocumented,” said the CTI expert.
He clarified that not everything is as shown on the CSI TV show.
Just as not everything that shines is gold, not everything that is touched becomes a mark.
However, if it can be used, if the respective matching is performed.
