Monti calls for time for markets and sacrifices for Italians
The future Italian head of government, Mario Monti, has asked for some time from the markets to form his team and launch a program that will include "sacrifices" aimed at regaining the credibility lost during the last months of the Berlusconi government.
The former European Commissioner debated with political parties yesterday and today met with trade unions and employers.
It should form a relatively restricted cabinet, composed of technocrats outside Parliament.
